{"type":"message","id":"8dc770fb","parentId":"11b8ed61","timestamp":"2026-04-02T02:05:46.776Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-04-02 04:05 GMT+2] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Teste die Tool Registry Implementation im Verzeichnis C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\crates\\tool-registry.\n\nFühre aus:\n1. `cargo check` - um Kompilierungsfehler zu finden\n2. `cargo test` - um Tests zu laufen lassen\n3. Liste alle Fehler auf\n4. Wenn Fehler gefunden werden, analysiere sie und schlage Korrekturen vor\n\nSei präzise bei den Fehlermeldungen und Zeilennummern."}],"timestamp":1775095546773}}
{"type":"message","id":"33d18ea5","parentId":"8dc770fb","timestamp":"2026-04-02T02:06:39.485Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Der Benutzer möchte, dass ich die Tool Registry Implementation im Verzeichnis `C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\crates\\tool-registry` teste. Ich muss:\n\n1. `cargo check` ausführen\n2. `cargo test` ausführen\n3. Alle Fehler auflisten\n4. Fehler analysieren und Korrekturen vorschlagen\n\nLass mich zuerst prüfen, ob das Verzeichnis existiert und was darin ist, dann `cargo check` und `cargo test` ausführen.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":" Ich werde die Tool Registry Implementation testen. Lass mich zuerst das Verzeichnis prüfen und dann die Rust-Build-Tools ausführen."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_ySyFp1z0R16oDdTq97E0M2Lw","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\crates\\tool-registry\\Cargo.toml"}},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_pnpwtfjhTeR2brlpppT0LSrr","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cargo check","workdir":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\crates\\tool-registry","timeout":120}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":8818,"output":224,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9042,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775095546776}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1ef5dc4","parentId":"33d18ea5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T02:06:39.550Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_ySyFp1z0R16oDdTq97E0M2Lw","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[package]\nname = \"tool-registry\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nedition = \"2021\"\nauthors = [\"Andrew (OpenClaw) <openclaw@ecc-framework.local>\"]\ndescription = \"Tool registry with file operations, bash execution, and MCP integration\"\nlicense = \"MIT\"\n\n[dependencies]\n# Async\nasync-trait = \"0.1\"\ntokio = { version = \"1.35\", features = [\"full\", \"process\"] }\n\n# Serialization\nserde = { version = \"1.0\", features = [\"derive\"] }\nserde_json = \"1.0\"\n\n# Error Handling\nthiserror = \"1.0\"\nanyhow = \"1.0\"\n\n# Tracing\ntracing = \"0.1\"\n\n# Regex for grep patterns\nregex = \"1.10\"\n\n# Glob for file patterns\nglob = \"0.3\"\n\n# Which for command lookup\nwhich = \"6.0\"\n\n[dev-dependencies]\ntokio-test = \"0.4\"\ntempfile = \"3.8\"\n\n[lib]\nname = \"tool_registry\"\npath = \"src/lib.rs\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775095599547}}
